cui_name: Nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide coenzyme Q reductase deficiency
reasoning: Complex I (NADH dehydrogenase) deficiency is a rare mitochondrial genetic disorder estimated at approximately 1-3 per 100k births globally. Heterogeneous group with highly variable clinical presentations ranging from infantile to adult onset. Limited systematic epidemiological data; incidence estimate based on case report frequency and small cohort studies rather than population registries. Using conservative mid-range estimate of 1.5 per 100k.
